title: Queue Simulation
statement:
# Queue Operations

Simulate queue operations and output the results.

## Problem Description

Perform a sequence of queue operations:
- ENQUEUE X: Add integer X to the back
- DEQUEUE: Remove front element
- FRONT: Print front element (or EMPTY if queue is empty)

## Input Format

First line: integer N (number of operations)
Next N lines: operations

## Output Format

Output of each FRONT operation, one per line.

## Constraints

- 1 ≤ N ≤ 1000
